Blade 9/6/2025 10:40 PM
Fire is a rapid oxidation process of a fuel in a chemical reaction known as combustion, which releases heat, light, and various products. It occurs when a combustible substance combines with oxygen in the presence of heat, resulting in flames and other reaction products. Fire is an exothermic reaction, meaning it produces heat, and it can convert materials like wood or gasoline into carbon dioxide and water.
